  "_comment": [
    "Hand-maintained. The Verb + Route judgement ADR-0009 says the generator cannot make —",
    "the 'fresh agent read' the §7 gate asks for. generate-parity-table.ts merges this onto",
    "the AST-derived rows to fill the Verb/Route/Notes columns of docs/generated/rpc-parity.*.",
    "",
    "Guard and Permissions stay generated from source; only Verb/Route/Notes come from here.",
    "'routes' must cover EXACTLY the 166 RPC actions — the generator fails the build on any",
    "drift, which is how a new RPC action is forced to receive a route judgement. A null verb",
    "means the action does NOT become an HTTP route; 'note' says why.",
    "'extra' are the four routes with no RPC counterpart (decision 36 / §7) — appended to the",
    "generated table as an addendum, not folded into the AST rows."
  ],
